ghtful discussions of key films as well as studio publicity and fan magazines, the essays in this collection analyze how these actors and actresses helped lift spirits during World War II, whether in service comedies, combat films, or escapist musicals. The contributors, all major writers on the stars and movies of this period, also explore how cultural shifts after the war forced many stars to adjust to new outlooks and attitudes, particularly in film noir. Together, they represented the hopes and fears of a nation during turbulent times, enacting on the silver screen the dreams of millions of moviegoers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aBlaetz, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuscombe, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCountryman, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Sean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHamad, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeil, Charlie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLugowski, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLean, Adrienne L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSedman, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWorland, Rick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081355084840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813550848423Coveruhttps://www.degruy